    {
      "id": "ioP9s84Sd4kXsz0UlLKnd",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2838.2398374683216,
      "y": 487.5379374490342,
      "width": 327.56768798828125,
      "height": 80,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aj",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 298072380,
      "version": 537,
      "versionNonce": 582238012,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780141183122,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When the status in Transaction table is \nupdated, we atomically update the status\nvalue in PaymentIntent table via ACID \ntransactions in sQL",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When the status in Transaction table is \nupdated, we atomically update the status\nvalue in PaymentIntent table via ACID \ntransactions in sQL",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "16mgRVc_30IEdgdy23ump",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1790.2212523196995,
      "y": 1042.117452424635,
      "width": 390.6236572265625,
      "height": 80,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ak",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1912875396,
      "version": 337,
      "versionNonce": 1092575876,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780141183122,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This doesn't happen on https\nand on a private line with strict\nsecurity measures and special hardware,\nhappens over a binary protocol or message format",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This doesn't happen on https\nand on a private line with strict\nsecurity measures and special hardware,\nhappens over a binary protocol or message format",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "44mS5KpC0f60KZGhB_w6o",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1297.818867747768,
      "y": 101.4337045080236,
      "width": 738.7833251953125,
      "height": 40,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "al",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2094545980,
      "version": 698,
      "versionNonce": 1826682812,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780141183122,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1) Is the person / merchant making the request really who they say they are ? (impersonation)\n2) Are we protecting customer's sensitive info like card details / password ?",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1) Is the person / merchant making the request really who they say they are ? (impersonation)\n2) Are we protecting customer's sensitive info like card details / password ?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4rXNn95jRQUUqEFnot4t7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1314.806401537283,
      "y": 1284.2394238952904,
      "width": 949.77868312794,
      "height": 760,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "am",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1596069892,
      "version": 1358,
      "versionNonce": 127431172,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780141183122,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1) Is the person / merchant making the request really who they say they are ? (impersonation)\n\nX-API-KEY : {key}\n\nInclude this in the REST api calls\nto identify the Merchant, we can\nstore this in our DB and compare.\n\nThis is of course not good design as it hackers\ncan sniff this key and replay payments / impersonate.\n\nAnother issue is when by mistake secrets are\nleaked on Github etc (by vibe coders). Anyone can \nuse it and do bad things.\n\n-------------------------------\n\nWhen a request comes in we first verify the signature using hash as below and with the private key stored\non our servers, then to know if it's being sent the 2nd time we look for nonce in cache and also the timestamp\nto compare when it's sent to prevent replay attacks.\n\n// Example request with signature to be used instead of only API_KEY\n{\n  \"method\": \"POST\",\n  \"path\": \"/payment-intents/{paymentIntentId}/transactions\",\n  \"body\": {\n    // body here\n  },\n  \"headers\": {\n    \"Authorization\": \"Bearer pk_live_51NzQRtGswQnXYZ8o\", // API Key\n    \"X-Request-Timestamp\": \"2023-10-15T14:22:31Z\", // Timestamp\n    \"X-Request-Nonce\": \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890\", // Nonce\n    \"X-Signature\": \"sha256=7f83b1657ff1fc53b92dc18148a1d65dfc2d4b1fa3d677284addd200126d9069\" // Hash of body\n  }\n}\n\nHMAC-SHA256(private_key, request) = signature, put in headers\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1) Is the person / merchant making the request really who they say they are ? (impersonation)\n\nX-API-KEY : {key}\n\nInclude this in the REST api calls\nto identify the Merchant, we can\nstore this in our DB and compare.\n\nThis is of course not good design as it hackers\ncan sniff this key and replay payments / impersonate.\n\nAnother issue is when by mistake secrets are\nleaked on Github etc (by vibe coders). Anyone can \nuse it and do bad things.\n\n-------------------------------\n\nWhen a request comes in we first verify the signature using hash as below and with the private key stored\non our servers, then to know if it's being sent the 2nd time we look for nonce in cache and also the timestamp\nto compare when it's sent to prevent replay attacks.\n\n// Example request with signature to be used instead of only API_KEY\n{\n  \"method\": \"POST\",\n  \"path\": \"/payment-intents/{paymentIntentId}/transactions\",\n  \"body\": {\n    // body here\n  },\n  \"headers\": {\n    \"Authorization\": \"Bearer pk_live_51NzQRtGswQnXYZ8o\", // API Key\n    \"X-Request-Timestamp\": \"2023-10-15T14:22:31Z\", // Timestamp\n    \"X-Request-Nonce\": \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890\", // Nonce\n    \"X-Signature\": \"sha256=7f83b1657ff1fc53b92dc18148a1d65dfc2d4b1fa3d677284addd200126d9069\" // Hash of body\n  }\n}\n\nHMAC-SHA256(private_key, request) = signature, put in headers\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
